## Git: one commit per phase plan step

When implementing any phase from `docs/PHASE_*_SPEC.md` or the Cursor plan:

1. Complete one plan step (e.g. "Step 5 — Face pipeline").
2. Verify (tests/build/smoke as appropriate).
3. `git add` only files for that step.
4. Commit: `type(scope): Phase N step M — short description`
5. Start the next step.

Never commit `.env`, `*.onnx`, `data/faces/`, or secrets. Push only when the user asks.
